-- IndusInd Bank, Satyam Computer Services, Urja Global: India Equity Preview
-- B y   M a d e l e n e   P e a r s o n   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 2010-09-22T02:41:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/indusind-bank-satyam-computer-services-urja-global-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex ,
gained 95.45, or 0.5 percent, to 20,001.55, surpassing 20,000
for the first time since January 2008. The S&P CNX  Nifty  Index
on the National Stock Exchange advanced 0.5 percent to 6009.05.
The  BSE 200 Index  increased 1.86, or 0.1 percent, to 2,529.08.
 SGX S&P CNX Nifty Index futures  for September delivery climbed
0.3 percent to 6,030.0 at 10:23 a.m. in Singapore.  Axis Bank Ltd.  (AXSB IN): India’s fourth-largest lender is
beating all local and international competitors in underwriting
the nation’s bond sales, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.
The stock fell 1 percent to 1,530.75 rupees.  Hero Honda Motors Ltd.  (HH IN): The nation’s biggest
motorcycle maker was downgraded to “neutral” from “buy” by
 Sonal Gupta , an analyst at  UBS AG . The brokerage set a price
estimate of 1,950 rupees per share. The stock fell 0.7 percent
to 1,809.05 rupees.  IndusInd Bank Ltd.  (IIB IN): The lender plans to raise as
much as 11.7 billion rupees ($256 million) selling 50 million
shares to large investors at 234.55 rupees apiece, it said in a
statement to the exchange. The stock rose 0.1 percent to 265.85
rupees.  Maruti Suzuki India Ltd.  (MSIL IN): Volkswagen AG may
extend its global partnership with Suzuki Motor Corp. in India
by tapping the manufacturing and design facilities of Maruti
Suzuki, India’s biggest carmaker, the Economic Times reported,
quoting two people familiar with the development. Maruti rose 1
percent to 1,413.1 rupees.  Satyam Computer Services Ltd.  (SCS IN): The software
exporter will report annual earnings this month, the first
detailing of yearly accounts since the company was embroiled in
the nation’s biggest corporate probe,  Sridhar Maturi , a
spokesman at the Hyderabad-based company, said in a telephone
interview yesterday. Satyam advanced 3.9 percent to 95.2 rupees.  Sun Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd.  (SUNP IN): Taro
Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. said Sun Pharmaceutical acquired
a controlling stake in Taro after reaching an agreement with the
Levitt and Moros families. Sun Pharmaceutical climbed 2.9
percent to 1,930.75 rupees.  Tata Motors Ltd.  (TTMT IN): The biggest truckmaker and
owner of Jaguar Land Rover is planning diesel and larger petrol
engines for the Nano car, the Financial Express newspaper
reported, citing an executive it didn’t identify. The stock
increased 2.2 percent to 1,080.6 rupees.  Urja Global Ltd.  (UGL IN): The power projects developer
decided to build a 200-megawatt solar-module manufacturing plant
and approved a plan to set up a 5-megawatt solar plant, the
company said in a statement to the exchange. The stock lost 1
percent to 99.8 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
